A target is presented. Upon a key press from the participant, the
target will move along the path (outlined path is not shown to participants).
The trial will end when the target finishes travelling along the path.
• The target's motion may be initiated through participant input or
begin automatically after a short time delay.
• The target can start at any location, complete any number of
repetitions along the path in any time duration.
• Data provides timestamps synced with coordinates reflecting the
target's travel progress, useful for mapping eye-tracking recordings.
